cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes a model that uses LSTM and CRF for NER. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as NER is a common task in AI research. "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the proposed model uses neural networks. Finally, "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) could be a relevant sub-category as NER is often used in information retrieval systems.
